  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Petroleum Downstream Tax Transparency in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Key Activities 1. Investigate the sale of illegal products on the local market and advocate for the effective tracking of all petroleum export trucks &#x2013; this will involve working with an investigative journalist from Multimedia Group and Africa Centre for Energy Policy (ACEP) team to generate evidence on the operations of the illegal trade for public discussion. This will involve tracking some of the operations to neighbouring countries to understand how the trade is done  2. Convene multi -stakeholder meeting with the Ministry of Finance and Energy to identify solutions and set target for resolving the challenges. The forum will seek to generate commitment from the Ministry of Energy and Finance on specific actions agreed by all stakeholders which ACEP will track to ensure that they are followed. 3. Radio discussions to increase public awareness of the illegal trade &#x2013;these discussions will encourage citizens to look out for export trucks which discharge products on the local market.</narrative>
  </description>
